description:
Unlocking Disaster
Aired on 09/10/2003, Narrated by: David Bamber
On 24 February 1989, United Airlines Flight 811, a Boeing 747-100, is flying above the Pacific Ocean when part of the right-side fuselage is ripped off, ejecting nine people from the aircraft and causing explosive decompression. The flight later lands safely at Honolulu without any more loss of life. An electrical short circuit caused the cargo door to open, creating the explosive decompression.
